OL,3,CHigh-tech spoon developed to enrich
OL,4,Clives of dementia patients
OL,6,FHe said: "A loss of taste can remove
OL,7,Fthe enjoyment of food which impacts
OL,8,Fpatient wellbeing as food plays such a
OL,9,Fsignificant role in our lives. This is
OL,10,Fespecially prevalent in patients who
OL,11,Flive alone or in public care homes
OL,12,Fwith more generalised nutrition.
OL,14,F"In a heartfelt disclosure, an
OL,15,Findividual shared that he only ate
OL,16,Ftoast for the past five years, as to
OL,17,Fhim there's no difference between
OL,18,Ftoast and a regular Sunday roast."
OL,20,FDr Morgner said the Tasty Spoon could
OL,21,Falso save the NHS money.
