OL,6,FHe added: "The development of a
OL,7,Ftechnological aid like the Tasty Spoon
OL,8,Fhas the potential to rekindle the
OL,9,Fpleasure of eating for those facing
OL,10,Ftaste-related challenges and therefore
OL,11,Fcontribute to better health as well as
OL,12,Fmitigating the expense of treating the
OL,13,Fside effects of poor nutrition for the
OL,14,FNHS."
OL,16,FThere are about 944,000 people in the
OL,17,FUK with dementia, with one in 11 over
OL,18,Fthe age of 65 suffering from the
OL,19,Fdisease.
